00:09:08.581 --> 00:09:09.982  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Tosaki] I told you not to move.

140
00:09:10.149 --> 00:09:11.884  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chuckles]

141
00:09:13.586 --> 00:09:17.056  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're not angry just because I wouldn't
share a little information, are you?

142
00:09:20.960 --> 00:09:21.928  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Go ahead, then.

143
00:09:23.095 --> 00:09:24.797  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've got nothing left to live for.

144
00:09:25.598 --> 00:09:27.667  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
As long as I can have one last cigarette.

145
00:09:31.971 --> 00:09:34.073  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chattering]

146
00:09:37.677 --> 00:09:38.945  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's gotten awfully quiet.

147
00:09:39.278 --> 00:09:41.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[reporter]
Security! What's going on in there?!

148
00:09:42.181 --> 00:09:43.950  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We can't contact anyone inside.

149
00:09:44.016 --> 00:09:44.951  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[guard] So, what now?

150
00:09:45.651 --> 00:09:47.853  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All we can do is wait for word to--

151
00:09:47.920 --> 00:09:48.788  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh?

152
00:09:51.958 --> 00:09:52.959  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who's that?

153
00:09:56.963 --> 00:09:59.098  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[newscaster]
<i>It appears that a man pushing a wheelchair</i>

154
00:09:59.165 --> 00:10:00.733  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>has come out of the laboratory!</i>

155
00:10:00.967 --> 00:10:02.335  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Could it be a staff member?</i>

156
00:10:03.336 --> 00:10:04.270  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kouma groans]

157
00:10:04.337 --> 00:10:05.371  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is bad.

158
00:10:06.038 --> 00:10:08.107  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The press is in danger out there.

159
00:10:10.176 --> 00:10:12.111  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man 1]
Hey, isn't that Tanaka in the wheelchair?

160
00:10:12.278 --> 00:10:14.847  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[woman 1]
Tanaka? The second Ajin in the country?

161
00:10:15.014 --> 00:10:17.383  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[man 2] There's no mistake.
-[man 3] Do you have a moment?

162
00:10:17.917 --> 00:10:19.785  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[woman 2] Just one question.
-[guard] Go back!

163
00:10:19.852 --> 00:10:21.754  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[all shouting indistinctly]

164
00:10:21.921 --> 00:10:23.923  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[man 4] Mr. Tanaka.
-[man 5] We've gotta get this.

165
00:10:23.990 --> 00:10:26.025  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man 6] What happened inside?

166
00:10:26.092 --> 00:10:27.927  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Sato]<i> The most important thing is timing.</i>

167
00:10:27.994 --> 00:10:29.795  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[man 7] Here.
-[man 8] What can you tell us?

168
00:10:29.862 --> 00:10:34.166  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Sato] <i>Kei Nagai's capture</i>
<i>and Ikuya Ogura's arrival in Japan.</i>

169
00:10:34.934 --> 00:10:37.837  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>So, there would be a lot of press</i>
<i>in one place.</i>

170
00:10:39.872 --> 00:10:41.774  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Today is that time.</i>

171
00:10:44.944 --> 00:10:45.845  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Today...

172
00:10:48.414 --> 00:10:49.281  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've--

173
00:10:49.782 --> 00:10:51.183  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've come here today

174
00:10:51.684 --> 00:10:54.854  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
because there's something
I want the public to know.

175
00:10:55.688 --> 00:10:58.791  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let me start by saying two things.

176
00:11:00.826 --> 00:11:03.062  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Tanaka]<i> What exactly is Sato planning?</i>

177
00:11:05.264 --> 00:11:07.099  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My name is Sato and...

178
00:11:09.435 --> 00:11:10.403  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm an Ajin.

179
00:11:10.670 --> 00:11:12.805  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[woman 1] Ajin?
-[woman 2] What are you trying to say?

180
00:11:12.872 --> 00:11:14.707  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[man 2] Is that true?
-[woman 3] You're Ajin?

181
00:11:14.774 --> 00:11:17.176  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[woman 4] Aren't you afraid
of being captured by the government?

182
00:11:17.243 --> 00:11:18.911  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are the two things you want to say?

183
00:11:21.113 --> 00:11:22.248  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The first is...

184
00:11:23.249 --> 00:11:25.418  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
there's a lot of false information
out there.

185
00:11:26.185 --> 00:11:27.353  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't let it fool you.

186
00:11:28.788 --> 00:11:32.058  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
In the early 2000s,
there was a big news story.

187
00:11:32.425 --> 00:11:34.060  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It caused quite a commotion.

188
00:11:35.227 --> 00:11:39.865  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As you all know,
it was the news of Koji Tanaka here.

189
00:11:40.232 --> 00:11:41.100  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man]<i> Koji.</i>

190
00:11:42.134 --> 00:11:43.235  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Hey, Koji.</i>

191
00:11:43.969 --> 00:11:46.072  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What is it? Why so pale?

192
00:11:47.139 --> 00:11:48.774  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Tanaka] Dad, I--

193
00:11:49.809 --> 00:11:50.776  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm an Ajin.

194
00:11:51.444 --> 00:11:52.378  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Really?

195
00:11:52.445 --> 00:11:54.213  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you sure it's not a mistake?

196
00:11:54.280 --> 00:11:56.048  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[father] Well, that's amazing!

197
00:11:56.749 --> 00:11:58.851  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What do you do
if you find out you're a Ajin?

198
00:11:58.918 --> 00:11:59.885  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[knock on door]

199
00:11:59.952 --> 00:12:00.820  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man 1] Excuse me!

200
00:12:00.986 --> 00:12:02.488  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Tanaka gasps]
[knocking continues]

201
00:12:02.855 --> 00:12:03.756  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man 2] Mr. Tanaka,

202
00:12:03.823 --> 00:12:05.825  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-please answer some questions!
-[man 2] Just a few!

203
00:12:05.891 --> 00:12:07.293  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man 1] You're in there, right? Hey!

204
00:12:07.960 --> 00:12:10.096  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[newsman] <i>It's been three days</i>
<i>since the disappearance</i>

205
00:12:10.162 --> 00:12:12.031  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>of Japan's second Ajin, Koji Tanaka.</i>

206
00:12:12.465 --> 00:12:16.368  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[TV host] <i>Our program has decided</i>
<i>to offer a reward for Koji Tanaka!</i>

207
00:12:16.735 --> 00:12:19.105  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[TV audience chattering excitedly]

208
00:12:20.739 --> 00:12:24.877  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Sato] <i>The media got carried away,</i>
<i>and a TV show even offered a reward.</i>

209
00:12:26.245 --> 00:12:29.248  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This time, the same thing happened
with Kei Nagai.

210
00:12:29.949 --> 00:12:32.451  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's been treated
like some kind of public event,

211
00:12:32.518 --> 00:12:35.421  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and the media is feeding this frenzy
all over again.

212
00:12:37.089 --> 00:12:39.425  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But you have no idea
what was waiting for him.

213
00:12:39.792 --> 00:12:40.993  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] Yes, we do!

214
00:12:41.127 --> 00:12:42.895  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[woman 1]
Is there a problem we should know?

215
00:12:43.062 --> 00:12:46.532  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's true, some people do feel
a little sorry for them.

216
00:12:46.799 --> 00:12:49.201  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
After all, people who've discovered
that they're Ajins

217
00:12:49.268 --> 00:12:53.038  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
have to be taken into government custody,
and then must live under their care.

218
00:12:53.806 --> 00:12:56.842  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I know that's what the government
has officially announced.

219
00:12:56.909 --> 00:13:00.012  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But I tell you, it's a lie.

220
00:13:00.513 --> 00:13:05.351  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The government is now conducting
inhumane experiments on Ajins.

221
00:13:06.051 --> 00:13:08.020  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And that's the second thing
I wanted to say.

222
00:13:08.187 --> 00:13:10.189  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[man] What are you saying?
-[woman 1] Urban legend!

223
00:13:10.256 --> 00:13:12.391  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
In 2005, a video was leaked

224
00:13:12.458 --> 00:13:15.528  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
of the American government
doing experiments on Ajins.

225
00:13:15.794 --> 00:13:19.064  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Many people feel that similar things
are happening right here as well.

226
00:13:19.131 --> 00:13:20.833  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[woman 2] But, Mr. Sato, tell us.

227
00:13:20.900 --> 00:13:22.501  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Did you actually fall for that hoax

228
00:13:22.568 --> 00:13:25.104  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and illegally enter the lab
to get Tanaka out?

229
00:13:25.171 --> 00:13:26.438  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] That's obviously a crime!

230
00:13:26.805 --> 00:13:28.073  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Except I have proof.

231
00:13:28.140 --> 00:13:29.275  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] All right, where is it?

232
00:13:29.842 --> 00:13:34.013  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, I've already uploaded it online.

233
00:13:34.180 --> 00:13:36.081  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[woman 1] Get my laptop!
-[man 1] Confirm this.

234
00:13:36.148 --> 00:13:38.117  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man 2]
Get online, quickly! Search for Ajins.

235
00:13:38.184 --> 00:13:39.285  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[woman 2] Come on, hurry up!

236
00:13:40.386 --> 00:13:41.487  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man gasps]

237
00:13:41.854 --> 00:13:42.855  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] It's uploaded!

238
00:13:43.088 --> 00:13:43.956  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grumbles]

239
00:13:44.957 --> 00:13:48.127  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Those videos are... top-secret data

240
00:13:48.194 --> 00:13:51.163  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
from the home computer
of a certain Ajin researcher.

241
00:13:51.330 --> 00:13:53.032  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man 1] Whoa. Is this video real?

242
00:13:53.098 --> 00:13:55.901  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man 2] I don't know,
but it looks pretty authentic to me.

243
00:13:56.535 --> 00:13:59.405  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Sato] This cannot be forgiven!
Don't you see that?!

244
00:14:00.372 --> 00:14:04.510  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm asking all of you here
to please protest with me.

245
00:14:06.345 --> 00:14:11.317  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
In two days, I will begin a protest
directly in front of the Ministry,

246
00:14:11.383 --> 00:14:13.452  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
so, please come fight with me!

247
00:14:14.987 --> 00:14:19.425  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
After all, there is that chance
that one of you could...

248
00:14:20.993 --> 00:14:23.062  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
turn out to be an Ajin like us.

249
00:14:27.032 --> 00:14:27.900  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do it.

250
00:14:30.202 --> 00:14:35.374  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You must do it
for... the happiness of us all.

251
00:14:44.316 --> 00:14:46.518  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasping and screaming]

252
00:14:49.121 --> 00:14:49.989  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[woman] What was that?

253
00:14:50.656 --> 00:14:52.124  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[all speaking indistinctly]

254
00:14:52.291 --> 00:14:53.325  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[woman] Did you get that?

255
00:14:53.659 --> 00:14:56.161  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man 1] Just stay in the front.
Can you get a shot?

256
00:14:57.129 --> 00:14:58.497  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[man 2] Look out!
-What was that?

257
00:14:58.564 --> 00:14:59.431  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man 2] Get down.

258
00:14:59.498 --> 00:15:01.333  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Sato, was that your--?

259
00:15:02.001 --> 00:15:02.668  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

260
00:15:03.035 --> 00:15:03.903  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man 2] Don't move.

261
00:15:07.473 --> 00:15:10.676  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>As for the incident at the laboratory</i>
<i>two days ago,</i>

262
00:15:10.943 --> 00:15:13.045  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>the words of the man calling himself Sato</i>

263
00:15:13.112 --> 00:15:15.447  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>were completely untrue</i>
<i>and without foundation.</i>

264
00:15:15.681 --> 00:15:20.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Also, we have just confirmed the deaths</i>
<i>of numerous guards, researchers,</i>

265
00:15:20.986 --> 00:15:23.055  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>and Dr. Ikuya Ogura, who was--</i>

266
00:15:23.122 --> 00:15:24.290  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[monitor turns off]

267
00:15:27.626 --> 00:15:29.295  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's today, right?

268
00:15:33.999 --> 00:15:35.935  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you going to do, Mr. Tosaki?

269
00:15:36.302 --> 00:15:38.537  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There will be a huge scene
in front of the Ministry.

270
00:15:40.039 --> 00:15:43.208  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, tell me... what should I do?

271
00:15:45.010 --> 00:15:45.978  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Doesn't matter.

272
00:15:46.612 --> 00:15:48.247  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nothing's going to change.

273
00:15:53.552 --> 00:15:55.587  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh? There's nothing here.

274
00:15:56.455 --> 00:15:57.990  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey, am I on TV?

275
00:15:59.124 --> 00:16:01.126  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[girl] They said there'd be a protest
or something.

276
00:16:02.428 --> 00:16:05.497  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[cameraman] What should we do?
-[director] Let's at least record

